Day in Donbass: 15 enemy shelling, two AFU fighters are wounded

01 Nov 2019, 05:23

The occupiers used mortars, grenade launchers, BMPs, machine guns and other small arms yesterday
On Thursday, October 31, fighters in Donbass 15 times violated the ceasefire regime.
The enemy fired at the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with 82 mm prohibited by the Minsk Agreements, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns, other small arms and BMP weapons.
This is stated in the morning news release of the United Forces operation.
In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "East" the enemy carried out seven shellings:

near Novogrigorovka and Nevelsky - machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
nearby Kamenka - hand-held anti-tank grenade launchers and small arms;
three times in the water district of the Azov region - with armaments BMP-1, small arms and grenade launchers of different systems;
near Lebedinsky - from large-caliber machine guns.

In the area of responsibility of tactical grouping "North" the enemy carried out eight shelling:

near Svitlodarsk - automatic grenade launchers;
twice near Lugansk - from large-caliber machine guns and machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Novolugansk - automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Crimean - from 82 mm mortars, automatic grenade launchers and large machine guns;
nearby the South - with anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Trinity - from large-caliber machine guns;
near Novotoshkivsky - 82 mm mortars.

Yesterday, October 31, one wounded member of the Allied forces was injured, another suffered a combat injury.
From the beginning of this day, armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries, in the area of responsibility of the tactical group "North", were firing Ukrainian positions near Lugansk with RPGs, large machine guns and other small arms.
